        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "First, (on the page [http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/docs\/quickstart\/create-a-model-and-database-table]) the script {{scripts\/load.sqlite.php}} won't work if ZendFramework is not in the php include path, it will throw fatal error on line \n{code}require_once 'Zend\/Application.php';{code}\nSolution:\ninsert following code \n{code}\/\/ Ensure library\/ is on include_path\nset_include_path(implode(PATH_SEPARATOR, array(\n    realpath(APPLICATION_PATH . '\/..\/library'),\n    get_include_path(),\n)));\n{code}\nbefore line {code}require_once 'Zend\/Application.php';{code}\n\nNext, there is a typo in the command of executing script.\nNow:\n{code}% php scripts\/load.sqlite.php{code}\nShould be:\n{code}% php scripts\/load.sqlite.php --with-data{code}\nNow the data will be inserted too.\n\nAnd the last one, script creates sqlite database file with the rights 600 on *nix, it should be changed to 666 to prevent errors in writing under different users (web server and command line).\nFix:\nafter line {code}$dbAdapter->getConnection()->exec($schemaSql);{code}\nadd {code}chmod($dbFile, 0666);{code}\n"
        },
