            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33130",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If quickstart exists on SVN,  I could some help for you by spellcheck, or code format..etc.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-01T18:40:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-01T18:40:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33132",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Doesn't http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/docs\/quickstart\/create-your-project fairly well tell you to add it to your include path?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-01T18:49:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-01T18:49:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33143",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=conf",
                        "name": "conf",
                        "displayName": "Shein Alexey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "2Dolf Schimmel:\nFirst, thank you for your time. Ok, let's look on that page.\n{quote}\nDownload the latest version of Zend Framework and extract the contents; make a note of where you have done so.\n*Optionally*, you can add the path to the library\/ subdirectory of the archive to your php.ini's include_path setting. \n{quote}\nAs you can see there is a word \"Optionally\". So, as I don't like to change my php.ini without extra need, I skipped this part.\nNext:\n{quote}\nAt this point, if you haven't added Zend Framework to your include_path, we recommend either copying or symlinking it into your library\/ directory. In either case, you'll want to either recursively copy or symlink the library\/Zend\/ directory of your Zend Framework installation into the library\/ directory of your project. On unix-like systems, that would look like one of the following: \n{code}\n# Symlink:\n% cd library; ln -s path\/to\/ZendFramework\/library\/Zend .\n\n# Copy:\n% cd library; cp -r path\/to\/ZendFramework\/library\/Zend .\n{code}\n{quote}\nSo I made symlink and all worked out of the box, as expected, excepting the script load.sqlite.php that relies on the settings in the include_path although this is optional behavior.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=conf",
                        "name": "conf",
                        "displayName": "Shein Alexey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-03T00:26:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-03T00:26:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33500",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ryandesign",
                        "name": "ryandesign",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This first item (about the include_path) is a duplicate of issue #7091.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ryandesign",
                        "name": "ryandesign",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-16T21:51:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-16T21:51:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33502",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ryandesign",
                        "name": "ryandesign",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To the second issue, I agree \"php scripts\/load.sqlite.php\" needs to be \"php scripts\/load.sqlite.php --withdata\" (note: not \"--with-data\"). This needs to be fixed in the \"do the following:\" code sample, but is already fixed in the \"You should see output like the following:\" section that follows.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ryandesign",
                        "name": "ryandesign",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-16T22:34:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-16T22:34:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33506",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=conf",
                        "name": "conf",
                        "displayName": "Shein Alexey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "2Ryan Schmidt: Thanks, for the answer, I really missed that issue #7091. What about the last enhancement about chmoding rights?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=conf",
                        "name": "conf",
                        "displayName": "Shein Alexey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-16T23:18:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-16T23:18:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ryandesign",
                        "name": "ryandesign",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with you about the third and final issue as well. On my Mac OS X system, files are by default created with 644 permissions, not 600 as they were for you, but either way, these are insufficient permissions for the web server to be able to write to the database, if I am the user who created it. Attempting to sign the guestbook results in this message:\n\nAn error occurred\nApplication error\nException information:\nMessage: SQLSTATE[HY000]: General error: 8 attempt to write a readonly database\n\nchmodding the guestbook database to 666 as you suggest is one possible fix for this, and is consistent with the existing instructions in the quickstart to chmod the data and data\/db directories to 777. I agree it would make sense for scripts\/load.sqlite.php to do this chmod for you after it creates the database.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ryandesign",
                        "name": "ryandesign",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-17T00:42:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-17T00:42:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33510",
